description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Senior Occupational Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Colliers Court, Cinderford (Forest of Dean)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – Band 6 £31,365-37,890 pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 22.5 hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gloucestershire Health and Care NHS Foundation Trust’s Complex Care at Home Team (CC@H) is an evolving service that focuses on promoting patient centered care and support in the community, using a health coaching approach. The Complex Care at Home Team also looks to the early identification of patients who are at risk of deteriorating health, wellbeing and/or frailty. The service works with patients and the multi-disciplinary team (MDT), including primary care, developing and delivering personalised care plans which support people to maintain their health and wellbeing, and prevent or delay crises. This includes promoting advanced care planning to enable appropriate responses should a crisis emerge.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Forest of Dean team consists of administrative staff, community matrons/case managers, health and wellbeing coordinators, a physiotherapist and a social care practitioner. We are now ready to recruit an additional therapist to complement our existing team and rapidly evolving service.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit a Senior Occupational Therapist to join the service and to work autonomously as part of the CC@H MDT. The post holders will deliver highly specialist clinical interventions to patients with multiple comorbidities who may be frail and have cognitive or memory problems. You will be part of a multi-professional team responsible for the delivery of effective case management.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Professional support will be provided by the network of OTs within the wider CC@H, the integrated care team within the locality and also the Professional lead for Occupational Therapy. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part of the role will involve the provision of education for the CC@H team to provide the team with skills to enable them to deliver appropriate OT based interventions, to help improve patients’ physical and psychological health.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be flexible, adaptable and thrive on responding positively to a challenging and changing environment &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you would like further information about this role please contact Sarah Shepherd, Community Matron, Complex Care at Home on 0300 421 6074 or Amy Wadley, Professional Lead Occupational Therapy 01452 425549&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Complexcareathome@glos-care.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shortlisting date: 13&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Proposed interview date: 20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
